sequenceDiagram
  participant API as Anthropic API<br/>(Streaming)
  participant STE as StreamingToolExecutor
  participant TOOL as Tool Execution
  participant UI as REPL UI

  Note over API,UI: API streams + tools execute in parallel

  API->>STE: stream: AssistantMessage (text)
  STE->>UI: yield message

  API->>STE: stream: tool_use block A (Read)
  STE->>STE: addTool(A) → queued
  STE->>STE: tryStartNext() → A is concurrencySafe
  STE->>TOOL: execute A (async)
  Note over STE: A status: executing

  API->>STE: stream: tool_use block B (Grep)
  STE->>STE: addTool(B) → queued
  STE->>STE: tryStartNext() → B concurrencySafe
  STE->>TOOL: execute B (async, parallel with A)

  API->>STE: stream: tool_use block C (Bash)
  STE->>STE: addTool(C) → queued
  STE->>STE: tryStartNext() → C NOT safe, blocked

  TOOL-->>STE: A progress update
  STE->>UI: yield progress (immediate, no buffering)

  TOOL-->>STE: A complete → results buffered
  Note over STE: A status: completed

  STE->>STE: getCompletedResults()
  STE->>UI: yield A results (in receive order)
  Note over STE: A status: yielded

  TOOL-->>STE: B complete
  STE->>UI: yield B results (next in order)
  Note over STE: B status: yielded

  STE->>STE: tryStartNext() → all concurrent done → C can start
  STE->>TOOL: execute C (exclusive access)

  API->>STE: stream ends (stop_reason)
  Note over STE: getRemainingResults()

  TOOL-->>STE: C complete
  STE->>UI: yield C results
  Note over STE: All tools yielded
